<item>
            <title>[JCR-3148] Using transactions still leads to memory leak</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-3148</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>This is a result of the way that &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-395&quot; title=&quot;Using transactions leads to memory leak&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JCR-395&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; was fixed. If you look at the code, you&amp;#39;ll see that txGlobal.remove(xid) is called as the last statement in both XASessionImpl.commit() and XASessionImpl.rollback(). However, in both methods an exception could be thrown either as a result of calling tx.commit() (or tx.prepare()) and tx.rollback(). &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
As a result, the transaction will not be removed from txGlobals whenever the commit or the rollback has failed for any reason. My suggestion would be to move the txGlobal.remove(xid) into a finally block.</description>
